text: Bolshesukhoyazovo () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Bolshesukhoyazovsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 604 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 31 km from Mishkino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Bolshesukhoyazovo
